abstract: Lebanon's newly designated prime minister said Friday he plans to form a government of experts and independents to deal with the country's crippling economic crisis. Hours after he spoke, riots by his opponents broke out in Beirut, leaving at least seven soldiers injured.
snippet: Lebanon's newly designated prime minister said Friday he plans to form a government of experts and independents to deal with the country's crippling economic crisis. Hours after he spoke, riots by his opponents broke out in Beirut, leaving at leas...
lead_paragraph: BEIRUT — Lebanon's newly designated prime minister said Friday he plans to form a government of experts and independents to deal with the country's crippling economic crisis. Hours after he spoke, riots by his opponents broke out in Beirut, leaving at least seven soldiers injured.
headline_main: Lebanon's New PM Says He Plans a Government of Experts
headline_print_headline: Lebanon's New PM Says He Plans a Government of Experts

abstract: Several factors unrelated to the facts are shielding President Trump in ways Nixon would have envied.
snippet: Several factors unrelated to the facts are shielding President Trump in ways Nixon would have envied.
lead_paragraph: Richard Nixon was a crafty president, at war with his political enemies but inclined to carry out most of his battles behind the scenes. Donald Trump trumpets his grievances, using public lashings to diminish his enemies and nip at allies who anger him. Nixon began his second term in January of 1973 with support from nearly 70 percent of the American people. Mr. Trump’s public approval has never hit 50 percent, according to the Gallup poll. Nixon saw his support steadily erode as details of the Watergate scandal trickled out. Mr. Trump’s support has held steady despite a fire hose of accusations. His approval rating stood at a typical 43 percent when the House opened its impeachment inquiry on Sept. 24.

abstract: The presidents of Belarus and Russia met Friday to discuss deeper economic ties between the two close allies amid mounting concerns in the Belarusian capital of Minsk that Moscow ultimately wants to subdue its neighbor.
snippet: The presidents of Belarus and Russia met Friday to discuss deeper economic ties between the two close allies amid mounting concerns in the Belarusian capital of Minsk that Moscow ultimately wants to subdue its neighbor.
lead_paragraph: MOSCOW — The presidents of Belarus and Russia met Friday to discuss deeper economic ties between the two close allies amid mounting concerns in the Belarusian capital of Minsk that Moscow ultimately wants to subdue its neighbor.
headline_main: Is Russia Eyeing Belarus Takeover? Integration Talks Deepen
headline_print_headline: Is Russia Eyeing Belarus Takeover? Integration Talks Deepen

abstract: The Wall Street bank would pay a fine of as much as $2 billion and have a subsidiary plead guilty to settle an inquiry into the looting of a sovereign wealth fund in Malaysia.

abstract: The European Union’s top court on Friday overturned a decision preventing fugitive former Catalan leader Carles Puigdemont from taking a seat in the European Parliament, in a fresh legal victory for secessionist politicians from the Spanish region.
snippet: The European Union’s top court on Friday overturned a decision preventing fugitive former Catalan leader Carles Puigdemont from taking a seat in the European Parliament, in a fresh legal victory for secessionist politicians from the Spanish region...
lead_paragraph: BRUSSELS — The European Union’s top court on Friday overturned a decision preventing fugitive former Catalan leader Carles Puigdemont from taking a seat in the European Parliament, in a fresh legal victory for secessionist politicians from the Spanish region.
headline_main: Catalan Separatist Politicians Win New EU Legal Victory
headline_print_headline: Catalan Separatist Politicians Win New EU Legal Victory

abstract: Iraq's top Shi'ite cleric, Grand Ayatollah Ali al-Sistani, said on Friday that an early election was the only way out of the current unrest gripping the country and a new government should be formed soon.
snippet: Iraq's top Shi'ite cleric, Grand Ayatollah Ali al-Sistani, said on Friday that an early election was the only way out of the current unrest gripping the country and a new government should be formed soon.
lead_paragraph: BAGHDAD — Iraq's top Shi'ite cleric, Grand Ayatollah Ali al-Sistani, said on Friday that an early election was the only way out of the current unrest gripping the country and a new government should be formed soon.
headline_main: Iraq's Sistani Says Early Election Only Way Out of Crisis
headline_print_headline: Iraq's Sistani Says Early Election Only Way Out of Crisis

abstract: Impeachment didn’t undermine democracy. It vindicated it.
snippet: Impeachment didn’t undermine democracy. It vindicated it.
lead_paragraph: When George W. Bush lost the popular vote to Al Gore in 2000 but became president anyway, he did so with almost 50.5 million votes. I didn’t know that number until I looked it up, because it would have been unimaginable for that president — even though he could be quite demagogic — to brandish it as proof that he represented some quasi-mystical conception of “the people,” in contrast to the nearly 51 million citizens who voted for his opponent.

abstract: On impeachment day, we saw that people are capable of doing extraordinary things in times of gloom.
snippet: On impeachment day, we saw that people are capable of doing extraordinary things in times of gloom.
lead_paragraph: The bipolar days are here, half the planet at its farthest remove from sunlight and warmth, the other half engulfed by fires and some of the hottest days ever recorded.

abstract: More than 99% of U.S. President Donald Trump's television ads have focused on impeachment this year, according to an analysis that shows how central the topic has become for his re-election campaign.
snippet: More than 99% of U.S. President Donald Trump's television ads have focused on impeachment this year, according to an analysis that shows how central the topic has become for his re-election campaign.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — More than 99% of U.S. President Donald Trump's television ads have focused on impeachment this year, according to an analysis that shows how central the topic has become for his re-election campaign.
headline_main: Almost All of Trump's TV Campaign Ads Discuss Impeachment: Report
headline_print_headline: Almost All of Trump's TV Campaign Ads Discuss Impeachment: Report
